[2]
Date: 26 Dec 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ABC Online [edited]
<http://www.abc.net.au/ra/news/stories/s1272145.htm>

Australia suspends beef imports from Brazil
-----------------------------------------------
Australia has suspended imports of beef from Brazil after a suspected case
of foot-and-mouth disease. The case has been reported on a property in a
state of the country which had been recognized as foot-and-mouth disease-free.
Agriculture Minister Warren Truss says Australia has only ever imported a
small sample of Brazilian beef for processing, but all import permits have
now been cancelled.
"We do not import beef from Brazil in any quantities, and so there's no
likelihood of there being significant quantities coming into Australia. But
any risk is too much risk in these circumstances, and so all import permits
have been cancelled forthwith."
--
